INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  'e95cda8b-5186-45b7-b742-b95ecdacf146',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Svelte and Core Web Vitals — How LCP, CLS, and INP React to Your Component Patterns$escape$,
  $escape$Svelte's reactivity model touches all three Core Web Vitals in non-obvious ways.

LCP suffers when hero content sits behind an `{#await}` block — the browser can't discover the image until the promise resolves, delaying paint. Fix it by eagerly loading critical assets and injecting `<link rel="preload">` via `<svelte:head>` so the browser fetches them during HTML parse.

CLS is a common transition trap. Applying `transition:fly` or `transition:slide` to above-the-fold elements causes layout shifts before stable geometry exists. Reserve space with CSS `aspect-ratio` or explicit `width`/`height` attributes. When toggling visibility, prefer `visibility: hidden` over `{#if}` for layout-holding elements — `{#if}` removes nodes from the DOM, collapsing their space.

INP in Svelte 5 is a rune reactivity cost problem. A `$derived` that recomputes a large filtered list on every keystroke runs synchronously and blocks the interaction response. Use `await tick()` inside event handlers to yield control back to the browser mid-update, letting Svelte flush pending DOM writes before continuing expensive work.$escape$,
  $escape$<script>
  import { tick } from 'svelte';

  let query = $state('');
  let results = $state([]);

  async function handleInput(e: Event) {
    query = (e.target as HTMLInputElement).value;
    await tick(); // yield before heavy work — improves INP
    results = heavyFilter(query);
  }
</script>

<svelte:head>
  <link rel="preload" as="image" href="/hero.webp" />
</svelte:head>

<!-- width/height prevent CLS; no transition: on LCP elements -->
<img src="/hero.webp" alt="Hero" width="1200" height="630" />
<input oninput={handleInput} placeholder="Search" />$escape$,
  $escape$typescript$escape$,
